Some people want to cancel the World Baseball Classic.  They say it's full of meaningless exhibition games, and players shouldn't get hurt right before the MLB season.  But these people couldn't be more wrong — because the WBC is essential to baseball's future.  Let me explain

5) But not everyone is happy with the format.  For example, Mets all-star Edwin Diaz recently signed a $100 million contract and will be out for the entire 2023 season after getting injured at the WBC.  Astros all-star Jose Altuve also broke his thumb and will now miss 2+ months.

7) Nearly 70 million people watched South Korea vs. Japan  —  vs. 12 million for the 2022 World Series.  62% of households in Puerto Rico watched their game vs. the Dominican Republic.  And more people attended WBC pool play than all Oakland A's home games last year combined.

9) So let's not lose sight of the bigger picture.  The talent level at this year's WBC is better than its ever been, and the results speak for themselves.  There is a playoff atmosphere at every game, and the world's best talent is on full display.  That's how you grow the game.

8) And the players love the WBC too.  Trea Turner won a World Series in 2019, and he said the WBC is the loudest crowd he has ever played in front of.  Randy Arozarena also said his HR in the WBC was "better than any home run [he] hit in the World Series."  And the list goes on.
